Sentencas: Low temperature processed composite cathodes for solid-state fuel cell (SOFC) have been developed, consisting of La0.6Sr0.4Ti0.1Fe0.9O3 and Ag, as low as 800 degrees C process temperature.
Titulo: Low temperature processed composite cathodes for Solid-oxide fuel Cells

Sentencas: Using micro-tubular design, the performances of the cathodes have been investigated at the operating temperatures of 650 and 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Low temperature processed composite cathodes for Solid-oxide fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell consists of NiO-Y stabilized zirconia (YSZ) as an anode (support tube), Sc stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) as an electrolyte, Gd doped ceria (GDC) for an inter-layer between the electrolyte and the cathodes.
Titulo: Low temperature processed composite cathodes for Solid-oxide fuel Cells

Sentencas: The single performance has varied depending upon the types of cathodes, and the composite cathode with 50 wt% La0.6Sr0.4Ti0.1Fe0.9O3 and 50 wt% Ag has shown comparable performance to the cell with standard LSCF-GDC cathode.
Titulo: Low temperature processed composite cathodes for Solid-oxide fuel Cells
